Due to the pandemic, we have made some changes to our daily procedures. Please review the document shared in this post.
Important information for those dropping their students off at the Jr./Sr. High School. Doors will not open until 7:45 to limit time in the Hallways. Students need to be dropped off at doors 3 and 4 in the South parking lot. Due to construction, buses will be unloaded at doors 1 and 2, so the main entrance needs to be clear so buses have room to park. At the end of the day, students being picked up will exit doors 4 and 6.
Please call the office if you have questions

First Church of Christ
July 23 at 7:44 PM ·

The Church families of the Randolph Southern Community will be giving out free school supplies for your children this Saturday morning from 10:00 to Noon. This distribution will be via a drive-thru at First Church of Christ (206 W. Church Street in Lynn). Please enter the church parking lot from the east end (North Garfield Street) and volunteers will direct you to the North and East entrances (see map). Available supplies will be given for preschool thru 6th grade. Limited supplies for Jr & Sr high school will also be available. Please use the South entrance of the church building to pickup supplies if you do not drive. Use the West entrance to select a backpack, if needed.

Only people with tickets will be allowed to attend. We are only allowed to have 250 people in the gym. KISS tv will broadcast the ceremony. A link to KISS tv is available on our website.

post_text:
Attention Seniors

We will have graduation practice Saturday July 11th from 10:30am - 11:30am. A lunch will be provided for you after practice. You must attend practice to participate in the ceremony.
I need to know who is able to attend graduation on July 11th. We will need to limit the number of people in the gym, so it is important that we know how many of you plan to attend. Let the high school office know by Friday May 29th if you plan to attend the July 11th ceremony.
If you cannot attend on July 11th, we will open the school on June 4th for you to come and receive your diploma. We will set up the backdrop and Mr. Bowsman and I will be here to hand you your diploma. I need to know who needs to come on June 4th so I can create a schedule for the night. Let me know by May 29th if you plan to attend on June 4th. We plan on starting at 6pm on June 4th, but that depends on the number attending.

post_text:
The last day of school is May 21st. All assignments need to be completed by the 21st. We will receive packets on the 22nd. Only 4 days left to finish all assignments.

Senior banners are available for pick up. Call the high school office to set up a time for pick up, or pick them up during chrome book drop off on the 21st and 22nd.

Chrome book drop off will be on May 21st & May 22. May 21st will be from 8:00 am to 3:00 pm. May 22nd will be from 12:00 noon until 7:00 pm. Please bring your chrome book to door #25 on the north side of the building. Someone will come and get your chrome book. We will also return any student supplies that have been left at school. Please make sure that the charger is in the chrome book case. You may also return any other items that belong to the school such as textbooks, library books, band instruments etc. If you have any assignments that need to be turned in, you may do that also. If you have any questions please contact Annette Wilson at 765-576-0969.

post_text:
WIFI Use

There is limited wifi available outside of the school building in the areas by doors 2, 3, and 4. Connection would be to the same network that you connect to inside the building with the same filtering. Students must use his/her username and password and must comply with Children’s Information Protection Act (CIPA). Everyone must maintain social distancing and recommendations made by the Indiana Department of Health. Compliance with guidelines must be followed in order to ensure safety. External internet access will stop if guidelines are not followed. This is a voluntary option for students and parents to access from automobiles. If you have any questions please contact Annette Wilson at annette@rssc.k12.in.us

post_text:
FAFSA Information

There will be a FAFSA Frenzy on April 4th online from 1-3 PM. Indiana Commission staff will be answering questions through Facebook, Twitter and Instagram.

There are many ways to complete the FAFSA -- including via mobile phone at FAFSA.gov or the myStudentAid mobile app. You can call INvested anytime at 317-715-9007 for assistance.

Students who fail to file the FAFSA by the April 15th deadline as a direct result of COVID-19 illness or disruption may submit an appeal to the Commission in ScholarTrack to waive the April 15th deadline. Students will need to explain in their appeal how they were unable to submit the FAFSA by the April 15th deadline either due to a lack of access to the application, or as a result of serious illness of the student or an immediate family member (student’s spouse, child, parent, guardian, grandparent or sibling).
